1
00:00:02,377 --> 00:00:04,045
[dragon growls]

2
00:00:06,757 --> 00:00:08,175
[Coco panting]

3
00:00:09,217 --> 00:00:10,636
[Coco grunts]

4
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:15,557
[dragon growls]

5
00:00:16,558 --> 00:00:18,352
[Coco panting]

6
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:25,274
- Isn't that...
- It is.

7
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:26,568
Richeh's hole again.

8
00:00:27,611 --> 00:00:29,403
[RICHEH] How many times is that?

9
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:30,989
[TETIA] I've already lost count.

10
00:00:30,990 --> 00:00:33,700
Come on, let's look
for a covered spot

11
00:00:33,701 --> 00:00:34,784
where we can hide.

12
00:00:34,785 --> 00:00:36,954
I think it's starting
to get colder.

13
00:00:38,706 --> 00:00:40,081
♪

14
00:00:42,417 --> 00:00:44,586
[dragon roars]

15
00:00:46,881 --> 00:00:48,172
[Tetia whimpers]

16
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,758
[dragon continues roaring]

17
00:00:52,928 --> 00:00:55,597
- [COCO] Um, Tetia.
- [TETIA] Huh?

18
00:00:57,933 --> 00:01:00,394
Your hat.
You dropped it earlier.

19
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:06,692
Oh... Thank you, Coco.

20
00:01:07,651 --> 00:01:08,693
[Tetia cries softly]

21
00:01:08,694 --> 00:01:11,488
[COCO] So, are you all right?

22
00:01:13,574 --> 00:01:16,242
No, how could you be?

23
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:18,578
I'm sorry. It's all my fault.

24
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:19,747
[Tetia gasps]

25
00:01:21,248 --> 00:01:22,416
No, I...

26
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:25,334
Wow, it's cold! You should wear
my cloak, Tetia,

27
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:27,254
I'll just snuggle up like this!

28
00:01:31,592 --> 00:01:32,718
[TETIA] Uh...

29
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,469
Coco?

30
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:37,180
It's nice.

31
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:40,475
Whenever I put it on,
it makes me feel really safe.

32
00:01:41,268 --> 00:01:42,394
♪

33
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:44,812
[COCO] No one would ever guess
that under that cloak,

34
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,731
I'm shaking with fear.

35
00:01:46,732 --> 00:01:48,482
I know I look like a witch,

36
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:50,985
and that gives me
the strength to be brave.

37
00:01:50,986 --> 00:01:54,488
With that in mind,
I want you to wear it now.

38
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:56,532
You'll be much more help
than I've been.

39
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:58,076
I'm sure.

40
00:01:58,077 --> 00:01:59,411
[Tetia cries]

41
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:01,203
[Coco gasps]

42
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,664
- [Tetia crying]
- [COCO] What's happening?

43
00:02:04,917 --> 00:02:06,543
What are they doing now?

44
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:08,587
[Coco gasps]

45
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:11,589
It's so warm.

46
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:12,966
A cloud? [gasps]

47
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:15,259
I'm sorry! I shouldn't have
looked at you

48
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,886
like you were
to blame for this!

49
00:02:16,887 --> 00:02:17,930
[COCO] Huh?

50
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,935
Please, no.
You weren't wrong.

51
00:02:23,936 --> 00:02:25,227
I am to blame.

52
00:02:25,228 --> 00:02:27,146
And you didn't
say it out loud, so...

53
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:30,190
Saying it with my eyes
is no better.

54
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:32,819
The truth is,
I just got really scared,

55
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:34,529
and took it out on you.

56
00:02:34,947 --> 00:02:36,447
You're the new girl.

57
00:02:36,448 --> 00:02:39,076
I'm supposed to be the one
protecting you.

58
00:02:39,743 --> 00:02:41,368
Tetia.

59
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:42,370
[Coco sniffles]

60
00:02:42,913 --> 00:02:45,748
[COCO] You are protecting me!
This spell's so nice and warm,

61
00:02:45,749 --> 00:02:47,500
I almost forgot
we were in danger!

62
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:49,920
Dragon? What dragon?
I'm taking a nap!

63
00:02:50,796 --> 00:02:52,046
[Tetia laughs]

64
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:55,342
You know, I created this spell
all by myself.

65
00:02:56,051 --> 00:02:57,551
Ever since I was little,

66
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:59,720
I've dreamed of napping
on a cloud.

67
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:01,806
So I've been
experimenting with it.

68
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:04,266
It's not finished yet, though.

69
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:07,645
When it is, I'd like to get it
approved for general use.

70
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:10,148
That way everyone will be
able to try it.

71
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:13,734
It's not a very useful spell,
but it's my dream,

72
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,653
and it's special to me.

73
00:03:15,654 --> 00:03:18,572
This is your cloak,
so I want you to wear it.

74
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:21,325
Hold onto it until the day
we become real witches.

75
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:24,245
Then we can all take off
our novice cloaks together.

76
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:25,873
Fair?

77
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:30,502
[Coco chuckles softly]

78
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,005
[both laugh]

79
00:03:34,006 --> 00:03:35,548
- [AGOTT] I heard all that.
- [both gasp]

80
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:36,717
[AGOTT]
If you want to lie on this,

81
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,177
it needs to be made from
a more substantive material.

82
00:03:39,178 --> 00:03:41,261
- [RICHEH] Too cold outside.
- [both gasp]

83
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:42,555
[RICHEH] I'm coming in.

84
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:43,931
[AGOTT] And in order
to fly on it,

85
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,975
you'd need something light
yet durable,

86
00:03:45,976 --> 00:03:47,685
like for instance, cotton.

87
00:03:47,686 --> 00:03:49,603
That'd just be a normal,
boring mattress!

88
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:52,023
Dreams are all well and good,

89
00:03:52,024 --> 00:03:54,109
but you can't escape reality.

90
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:57,738
We should discuss how
we're getting out of here, yes?

91
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:01,281
This whole area seems to be
under some manner of spell,

92
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:03,159
which is why
no matter where we go,

93
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,369
we end up back
in the same place.

94
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:08,372
And all magic,
even the forbidden kind,

95
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,584
requires a Casting Seal
in order to work.

96
00:04:11,085 --> 00:04:13,794
We need to find out
where it is so that we can...

97
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,172
Uh?

98
00:04:15,881 --> 00:04:18,883
I think I saw it!

99
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:20,177
Earlier.

100
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:24,472
[AGOTT] You're right.
There it is.

101
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:26,306
[RICHEH] Sure enough.

102
00:04:26,307 --> 00:04:27,892
That's a Casting Seal.

103
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,227
Does, uh...

104
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:32,270
Does that dragon look like
it's gotten bigger?

105
00:04:32,271 --> 00:04:34,857
Either that
or we're all getting smaller,

106
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:36,526
and so's the space.

107
00:04:37,111 --> 00:04:40,571
Regardless, if the dragon
is protecting the Casting Seal,

108
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:41,948
we'll have to beat it.

109
00:04:41,949 --> 00:04:43,909
- A bit of fire magic should--
- [COCO] Sorry, but!

110
00:04:44,952 --> 00:04:49,206
Your last fire spell
didn't do that much damage.

111
00:04:49,873 --> 00:04:52,041
- [AGOTT] Oh?
- Let me explain!

112
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:53,667
You slowed it down,

113
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,170
but I don't think
you actually hurt it,

114
00:04:56,171 --> 00:04:57,463
which means...

115
00:04:57,464 --> 00:05:00,466
We have to find something
it will respond to.

116
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:01,676
[Agott gasps]

117
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:04,595
Then, how do you propose
we beat it?

118
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:05,846
[COCO] We don't.

119
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:07,057
[ALL] Uh?

120
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:10,477
[ALL] Huh?

121
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:11,852
[Agott inhales deeply]

122
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:13,063
[AGOTT] What is this?

123
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,106
Are you still mad at me
about what I said before?

124
00:05:15,107 --> 00:05:16,732
No, no, I'm not mad!

125
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,235
You and Tetia just gave me
an interesting idea.

126
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:20,403
[BOTH] Huh?

127
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,614
[COCO] I have a plan.

128
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:25,241
I don't know
if it'll work, but...

129
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:26,659
Let's try it.

130
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,869
♪

131
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:30,289
[scribbling]

132
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:34,167
[Tetia exclaims]

133
00:05:34,168 --> 00:05:35,751
You mean it?

134
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,295
Yes!

135
00:05:37,296 --> 00:05:40,547
We'll make Tetia's dream
a reality!

136
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:42,133
[Tetia exclaims]

137
00:05:42,134 --> 00:05:43,509
What are you suggesting?

138
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:47,429
[COCO] Well, in Tetia's cloud,
we felt safe and warm

139
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:49,098
even in the bitter cold, right?

140
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:52,685
So, if we were to make
a cloud bed for the dragon,

141
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:54,895
it might get comfortable
and decide to stay there

142
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:56,314
instead of attacking us!

143
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:57,274
Really?

144
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,317
- Well, that sounds rather--
- Brilliant.

145
00:05:59,318 --> 00:06:02,611
[RICHEH] None can withstand
the lure of a warm bed!

146
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:04,488
Not even dragons, probably!

147
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:05,949
Well said!

148
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:09,368
Uh, I don't know.

149
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:13,497
Give me a moment, please.
Let me think.

150
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:14,707
- Now...
- [Tetia giggles]

151
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:16,877
Humans love warm beds.
This we know.

152
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:22,715
[TETIA] Coco, are you all right?

153
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:24,925
[COCO] Me? Yes, I'm fine.

154
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:26,552
I was actually
wondering about

155
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:28,595
how the dragon
is doing right now.

156
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:29,805
[BOTH] Huh?

157
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:32,058
- The dragon?
- [COCO] Remember?

158
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:34,227
We were running away
from it, and then...

159
00:06:34,228 --> 00:06:37,771
It slammed into a pillar,
really hard, nose-first.

160
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:39,357
At the time,
all I could think about

161
00:06:39,358 --> 00:06:40,941
was how afraid I was.

162
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:42,651
But it must've hurt so much!

163
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,611
Now I feel bad
for the poor dragon.

164
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:45,988
[Agott sighs]

165
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:49,243
[COCO] And that's why
I like my plan.

166
00:06:50,202 --> 00:06:52,786
So let's try!
I know it might not work,

167
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:53,914
but what do we have to lose?

168
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,252
Master told me something.

169
00:06:59,253 --> 00:07:01,670
He said the spells which have
not been forbidden

170
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:05,132
are the ones that hold
the power to bring happiness.

171
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,424
So...

172
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:09,887
I want to show the dragon
some gentler magic.

173
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:11,555
If this does work,

174
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:14,059
that means no one
will have to get hurt.

175
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:18,271
Not any of us,
and not the dragon!

176
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:19,522
♪

177
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:23,234
[TETIA] Good point!

178
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:25,694
And if Agott decides
to help us,

179
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:28,697
then our chances of success
are even better, right?

180
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:31,326
Your eyes look like
you have an idea.

181
00:07:33,036 --> 00:07:34,413
[AGOTT] Is that so?

182
00:07:35,247 --> 00:07:36,538
Perhaps I do.

183
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,792
[TETIA] Right then,
let's work together.

184
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:42,628
You're the best of us
at drawing seals, after all.

185
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:44,004
That's obvious.

186
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:46,925
So with you on our team,
we can't lose!

187
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:50,345
[Agott inhales]

188
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,139
[exhales]

189
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:56,851
[AGOTT] Well...

190
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:01,647
Let's try it, then.

191
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:03,941
[COCO] Yay! [yelps]

192
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:05,152
[AGOTT] Watch out!

193
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,238
[Tetia sighs]

194
00:08:08,613 --> 00:08:09,905
[COCO] Thank you, Agott!

195
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,407
[AGOTT] Never mind that!

196
00:08:11,408 --> 00:08:12,908
Let's discuss our strategy!

197
00:08:12,909 --> 00:08:14,535
[Tetia giggles] All right!

198
00:08:17,331 --> 00:08:19,915
[AGOTT] You want to be able
to lie on it, correct?

199
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,292
[TETIA] Yes!

200
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:23,919
Just like a nice,
fluffy bed!

201
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:26,088
[AGOTT]
A material soft as a cloud,

202
00:08:26,089 --> 00:08:28,382
- but with the necessary heft.
- [TETIA] Hmm...

203
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:30,717
Something we can find
in the area...

204
00:08:30,718 --> 00:08:34,014
that would be able to withstand
the full weight of a dragon.

205
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:36,765
[gasps] Shredded paper!

206
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:39,477
No, our four Quires
wouldn't provide nearly enough.

207
00:08:39,478 --> 00:08:41,020
- Our clothes!
- Our hair.

208
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:42,438
Still not enough.

209
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:44,064
And you don't want
to give those up, do you?

210
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,275
[Richeh and Coco grunt]

211
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:49,321
- [AGOTT] Sand, though.
- [ALL] Huh?

212
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:52,366
If only we... [gasps]

213
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,241
The Wall Breaker spell!

214
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:56,452
We can create a fine sand

215
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:58,536
by demolishing
the walls and floors.

216
00:08:58,537 --> 00:08:59,706
[TETIA] That's perfect!

217
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,582
Who doesn't enjoy lying around
on a sandy beach?

218
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,335
Smart thought, Agott!

219
00:09:04,336 --> 00:09:06,504
[AGOTT] And the more signs
drawn to the seal,

220
00:09:06,505 --> 00:09:07,629
the finer the sand.

221
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,756
Especially with smaller seals.

222
00:09:09,757 --> 00:09:12,801
If it's tiny seals you need,
then just leave it to me!

223
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,345
Look at the speed!

224
00:09:14,346 --> 00:09:16,431
This is Richeh's specialty!

225
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,474
Tetia, from you,
I'll need a spell

226
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:21,268
to gather the sand in the plaza
without packing it too hard.

227
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:23,020
I'll get to work
on an enveloping spell

228
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:24,730
that will keep it in place.

229
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:26,106
Yes, ma'am!

230
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:28,276
- [COCO] Um, Agott?
- [AGOTT] Huh?

231
00:09:29,194 --> 00:09:30,861
Is there anything I can do?

232
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:32,239
[AGOTT] There isn't, no.

233
00:09:33,532 --> 00:09:36,825
I have agreed to your plan,
but at your current skill level,

234
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:39,286
I can't trust you to help
with the magic.

235
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:41,622
You'd do well
to stay out of our way.

236
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:52,426
[Coco gasps softly]

237
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,302
[COCO] Such a perfect circle.

238
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:56,846
How does she do it?

239
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:18,284
[COCO] She practices the circle
in the air a few times,

240
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:20,870
then starts at the point
closest to her.

241
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:24,165
Do Tetia and Richeh
use that technique as well?

242
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:33,006
[COCO]
And how have I been doing it?

243
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,716
Where to start...

244
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:36,302
The final shape...

245
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:39,055
I guess I never thought
about those things.

246
00:10:41,433 --> 00:10:43,142
I'll try it.

247
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:46,061
And until...
I can do it like they can.

248
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,355
♪

249
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:49,316
I'll keep trying!

250
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:53,277
Like this... Right?

251
00:10:53,278 --> 00:10:55,155
Then this...

252
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:04,331
[dragon roaring]

253
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,001
[roaring continues]

254
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:10,920
[Richeh breathing shakily]
It's cold.

255
00:11:11,463 --> 00:11:14,798
Yes, and it's gotten dark.
Shall I start a fire?

256
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,342
[RICHEH] I'm all out of paper.

257
00:11:16,343 --> 00:11:18,552
- [TETIA] So am I.
- [Agott groans]

258
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,387
[AGOTT] No, it won't work.

259
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,932
A Sign of Convergence
would pack it too hard.

260
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:25,643
What if you wrap it
in a membrane of air?

261
00:11:25,644 --> 00:11:27,685
[AGOTT] Too weak.
It would fall apart.

262
00:11:27,686 --> 00:11:29,022
[Tetia groans]

263
00:11:29,147 --> 00:11:31,357
[RICHEH] Reinforce it
with fine strips of cloth, then.

264
00:11:31,358 --> 00:11:33,775
[AGOTT] I'm afraid that won't be
enough to make a difference.

265
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:35,486
And it's going to get
even colder, so...

266
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:36,655
[RICHEH] Never mind.

267
00:11:36,863 --> 00:11:39,697
[Tetia groans] Come on,
there has to be something.

268
00:11:39,698 --> 00:11:41,699
- [Agott sighs]
- [TETIA] What to do, what to do.

269
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:44,871
[AGOTT] There must be a way.
Some perfect plan.

270
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:50,210
[Coco gasps]

271
00:11:51,378 --> 00:11:52,710
I...

272
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:54,422
I did it!

273
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:56,674
[both gasp softly]

274
00:11:56,675 --> 00:11:58,133
Ah, brilliant.

275
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:01,220
- But how exactly does--
- Completely stable.

276
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:03,180
She cast a Pyreball!

277
00:12:03,181 --> 00:12:04,891
Yours used to fizzle right out!

278
00:12:05,684 --> 00:12:07,685
When did you learn
to cast it so well?

279
00:12:07,686 --> 00:12:09,769
Now. I just watched all of you,

280
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:11,980
and then I practiced,
over and over.

281
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:15,526
I kept trying, till finally...

282
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:16,943
[Tetia exclaims]

283
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:20,615
How wonderful!
You really did it, Coco!

284
00:12:21,908 --> 00:12:22,949
Please...

285
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:24,702
Given enough time
and repetition,

286
00:12:24,703 --> 00:12:26,745
anyone would be able to...

287
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:30,083
Enough repetition?

288
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,750
[Agott gasps]
That's it! I've got it!

289
00:12:32,751 --> 00:12:34,086
[all gasp]

290
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:35,422
♪

291
00:12:40,301 --> 00:12:41,635
[AGOTT] Are we ready?

292
00:12:41,636 --> 00:12:44,054
- [COCO] Hm.
- You just say the word.

293
00:12:44,055 --> 00:12:45,390
[Agott inhales deeply]

294
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:47,057
[AGOTT] Let's go!

295
00:12:47,058 --> 00:12:48,268
♪

296
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:57,736
[TETIA] Coco!

297
00:12:57,985 --> 00:12:59,070
[COCO] Thank you!

298
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:01,863
[AGOTT]
It's definitely grown larger.

299
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,866
- We must finish this quickly!
- [dragon growls]

300
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:06,411
- [AGOTT] Richeh, go!
- [RICHEH] Right.

301
00:13:09,664 --> 00:13:11,082
[Coco panting]

302
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,627
♪

303
00:13:42,781 --> 00:13:45,116
[gasps softly] Done. Coco!

304
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:50,203
It's time.

305
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:52,415
- Signal to close the rings.
- [RICHEH] Hm.

306
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:55,626
- [RICHEH] Three...
- [COCO] Two...

307
00:13:55,627 --> 00:13:56,919
[COCO AND RICHEH] One.

308
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:06,680
[AGOTT] Next station.

309
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:20,193
[dragon growling]

310
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:27,033
[dragon roars]

311
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:33,789
- [COCO] It noticed!
- [TETIA] We need to meet up!

312
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:35,290
[AGOTT] You finished your rings?

313
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,709
[RICHEH] And activated them.

314
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:39,503
- Good. [pants]
- [TETIA] Repetition?

315
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:40,878
[AGOTT] Yes.

316
00:14:40,879 --> 00:14:43,507
In order to prevent
the spell from falling apart,

317
00:14:43,508 --> 00:14:45,050
we'll wrap it
in repetition magic

318
00:14:45,051 --> 00:14:47,636
that constantly returns it
to its initial form.

319
00:14:47,637 --> 00:14:49,013
That is...

320
00:14:49,222 --> 00:14:52,182
by enveloping the Wall Breaker
and Billow Cluster combination

321
00:14:52,183 --> 00:14:54,100
within a Repetition Spell,

322
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:56,019
we'll create a cloud of sand.

323
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,188
Based upon the size
of the dragon,

324
00:14:58,189 --> 00:15:00,065
I should think we'll need five.

325
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:01,899
If we can properly synchronize

326
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:05,028
the positioning and timing
to combine five into one,

327
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:07,323
even if it sinks
with the beast's weight,

328
00:15:07,741 --> 00:15:10,534
the sand cloud will keep
returning to its original shape,

329
00:15:10,535 --> 00:15:13,120
and maintain
the same downy quality.

330
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,205
[BOTH] It's called...

331
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:18,752
[dragon roars]

332
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:26,634
[BOTH]
The Dragon Disabler Duvet!

333
00:15:27,552 --> 00:15:29,845
Actually, it's the
Serpent's Bed of Sand.

334
00:15:29,846 --> 00:15:32,305
Another smart thought
from Agott!

335
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:34,350
- Agott to agree.
- [AGOTT] Enough silliness!

336
00:15:34,851 --> 00:15:36,769
This is our chance
to get past it!

337
00:15:36,770 --> 00:15:37,978
[dragon snores]

338
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:42,441
- [COCO] Tetia?
- [TETIA] Hm?

339
00:15:42,442 --> 00:15:44,651
- [COCO] Something wrong?
- [Tetia chuckles]

340
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:45,862
[TETIA] Nothing at all.

341
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:48,782
I just couldn't help but look.

342
00:15:49,908 --> 00:15:53,244
That dragon looks really happy
right now, doesn't it?

343
00:15:53,952 --> 00:15:56,496
You know,
I think this is the first time

344
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:59,082
my magic has ever made
someone happy.

345
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,376
[Coco chuckles softly]

346
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,212
[Tetia chuckles softly]

347
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:07,550
I never knew it could make me
so happy as well!

348
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:10,303
[dragon growling]

349
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:17,183
- [AGOTT] Well...
- [COCO] Yes.

350
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:19,144
This must be it.

351
00:16:19,145 --> 00:16:20,854
What kind of spell is it?

352
00:16:20,855 --> 00:16:22,522
No kind that I've seen.

353
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:23,650
[AGOTT] Hm...

354
00:16:23,858 --> 00:16:26,193
- I imagine Master might know.
- [Qifrey panting]

355
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:29,822
[brushbuddy sniffs]

356
00:16:29,823 --> 00:16:30,948
[brushbuddy squeaks]

357
00:16:30,949 --> 00:16:32,825
[QIFREY] Did they come this way?

358
00:16:32,826 --> 00:16:34,910
[brushbuddy squeaks, sniffs]

359
00:16:34,911 --> 00:16:36,662
No trace of them.

360
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:38,163
Did they move on already?

361
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:39,331
[TARTAH] Wait.

362
00:16:39,332 --> 00:16:41,207
Wasn't this alley paved?

363
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:43,543
I remember flagstones here.

364
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,420
Guess they were removed
at some point.

365
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:46,464
[Qifrey gasps]

366
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:49,926
[QIFREY] Brushbuddies are drawn
to the smell of Conjuring Ink.

367
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:51,636
[gasps] Is this...

368
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:54,305
[Tartah grunts]

369
00:16:55,306 --> 00:16:56,473
[QIFREY] Get back!

370
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:57,600
[Tartah grunts]

371
00:17:03,857 --> 00:17:06,442
[all screaming]

372
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:09,194
[AGOTT] How could you have
broken the seal

373
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:11,196
so spontaneously?
What were you thinking?

374
00:17:11,197 --> 00:17:13,615
[TETIA] I was thinking we needed
to break the seal!

375
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,074
[COCO] Everyone, look up there!

376
00:17:15,075 --> 00:17:17,076
I can see the sky!

377
00:17:17,077 --> 00:17:19,412
- A way out! It has to be!
- [dragon growls]

378
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:20,832
[AGOTT] Coco, get down!

379
00:17:25,043 --> 00:17:26,546
[screaming]

380
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:28,506
[COCO] Ago...

381
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:32,175
[AGOTT] Oh, no!

382
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:33,887
Without my Sylph Shoes...

383
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:36,723
I'm in a spot of trouble here.

384
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:40,727
[dragon growls]

385
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:48,859
[Agott grunts, gasps]

386
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:50,027
[AGOTT] Master?

387
00:17:50,028 --> 00:17:52,278
A dragon, well...

388
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:55,657
- [AGOTT] Master, I...
- Not now. It's coming.

389
00:17:55,658 --> 00:17:57,284
[dragon growling]

390
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,835
Hold on tight.
I need my hands free.

391
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:08,629
[AGOTT] Right!

392
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,552
♪

393
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:39,827
[dragon growling]

394
00:19:05,143 --> 00:19:06,311
[Qifrey sighs]

395
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:08,187
You should be safe now.

396
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:10,066
It appears to be unconscious.

397
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:14,277
- Agott?
- [gasps] Oh, sorry?

398
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:15,613
[Tetia cries] Master!

399
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:18,239
- You came to save us, thank you!
- [QIFREY] Tetia! Richeh!

400
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,700
How were you able
to get here, Master?

401
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:22,494
I was trying to find all of you,

402
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:24,830
and the space suddenly
opened up around me.

403
00:19:24,831 --> 00:19:26,082
[Qifrey gasps softly]

404
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,668
[QIFREY] Where's Coco?

405
00:19:29,502 --> 00:19:30,920
♪

406
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:36,049
[WITCH] Greetings, Coco.

407
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:38,760
So long have I waited

408
00:19:38,761 --> 00:19:43,765
for the seed I planted
to finally sprout.

409
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:47,560
Were you pleased with
the assignment I gave you?

410
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:49,897
Did it help you in your growth?

411
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,357
Ah, yes!

412
00:19:52,358 --> 00:19:54,568
I have a gift for you.

413
00:19:55,193 --> 00:19:58,155
I'll teach you
all sorts of things

414
00:19:58,156 --> 00:20:00,073
Qifrey never could.

415
00:20:00,074 --> 00:20:02,283
And when the time comes...

416
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:07,289
Ah... what a day
it shall be!

417
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:13,462
[TETIA] Coco! Coco!

418
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:16,007
[TETIA] Coco!

419
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:17,591
[Coco groans]

420
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:19,216
[Tetia exclaims]

421
00:20:19,217 --> 00:20:22,638
[COCO]
Master Qifrey, everyone...

422
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:27,935
- [gasps] Where's Agott--
- I'm here.

423
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:30,103
[AGOTT]
Thank you for this, Tartah.

424
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:31,189
Oh, it's nothing.

425
00:20:31,313 --> 00:20:33,816
I'll see if I can get
Grandad to come by.

426
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:36,818
- Thank goodness.
- [footsteps]

427
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:39,196
Are we in Kalhn?

428
00:20:39,197 --> 00:20:42,157
[TETIA] Yes, we made it back
safe and sound!

429
00:20:42,158 --> 00:20:43,909
[QIFREY] It's fortunate
I found you.

430
00:20:43,910 --> 00:20:46,619
You were unconscious
on the tower stairs.

431
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:48,414
[COCO] The stairs?

432
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:50,498
Wait. Your memory.

433
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,209
Did the Brimmed Caps
do something to you?

434
00:20:52,210 --> 00:20:55,921
No! I think I just need
to regain my bearings.

435
00:20:55,922 --> 00:20:57,215
That's all.

436
00:20:57,548 --> 00:20:58,799
[Coco gasps]

437
00:21:03,096 --> 00:21:05,097
- [TETIA] Coco?
- [COCO] Huh?

438
00:21:05,098 --> 00:21:06,891
Are you all right?

439
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:12,188
[gasps] Yes. I'm perfectly fine
now that I...

440
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,983
[Coco cries]

441
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:27,578
[Coco cries] I'm so sorry.

442
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:33,667
I put all of you in danger.

443
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:38,714
I'm really, really sorry.

444
00:21:43,761 --> 00:21:45,762
[QIFREY] Tetia filled me in

445
00:21:45,763 --> 00:21:47,639
on how you found
yourselves there.

446
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,391
The actions you took.

447
00:21:49,892 --> 00:21:51,184
All of it.

448
00:21:51,185 --> 00:21:52,686
[Coco breathes shakily]

449
00:21:54,147 --> 00:21:57,232
[QIFREY] It sounds to me
as though you saved everyone.

450
00:21:57,233 --> 00:21:58,442
[Coco gasps]

451
00:21:58,651 --> 00:22:01,318
You see, in magic,
the idea behind a spell

452
00:22:01,319 --> 00:22:03,404
is as important as
one's penmanship.

453
00:22:03,405 --> 00:22:06,242
Let's work hard
to nurture that talent.

454
00:22:06,784 --> 00:22:08,493
[Coco breathes shakily]

455
00:22:08,494 --> 00:22:10,621
[Coco whimpers]

456
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,293
[Coco chuckles softly]

457
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:20,422
Right!

458
00:22:21,841 --> 00:22:25,426
Oh, Coco! I'm so relieved
that you're safe!

459
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,386
[COCO] I'm sorry
for worrying you!

460
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:28,930
You too, Richeh and Agott.

461
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:29,932
[Nolnoa laughs]

462
00:22:30,141 --> 00:22:32,517
[NOLNOA] Not only safe,
but full of energy!

463
00:22:32,518 --> 00:22:34,644
[QIFREY] Indeed,
thanks to your help.

464
00:22:34,645 --> 00:22:36,437
The hour has grown quite late.

465
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:38,815
If I may, I would suggest
you stay at an inn tonight--

466
00:22:38,816 --> 00:22:39,858
[QIFREY] Mr. Nolnoa.

467
00:22:39,859 --> 00:22:42,777
I have a favor
I must ask of you.

468
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:44,321
[NOLNOA] Oh?

469
00:22:44,322 --> 00:22:47,448
[QIFREY] There's a Casting Seal
drawn on the back of this.

470
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:48,992
It would be very helpful to me

471
00:22:48,993 --> 00:22:50,910
if I could know what the ink
was made from.

472
00:22:50,911 --> 00:22:52,330
Would you investigate?

473
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:55,748
[NOLNOA] I see. The ink, eh?

474
00:22:55,749 --> 00:22:59,544
[QIFREY] And please, do not tell
the Knights Moralis about this.

475
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:01,420
[gasps] Come now!

476
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:02,881
We have a duty, you know!

477
00:23:02,882 --> 00:23:04,842
Forbidden Magic
sightings must be... Uh?

478
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:08,803
You will tell no one.

479
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:11,056
Not a soul.

480
00:23:11,057 --> 00:23:13,558
[high-pitched ringing]

481
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:14,894
[Nolnoa gasps]

482
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:18,105
[Nolnoa sighs]

483
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:21,440
[Nolnoa sighs]

484
00:23:21,441 --> 00:23:22,568
[NOLNOA] My...

485
00:23:23,027 --> 00:23:24,777
Just what is happening here?

486
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:25,820
[TARTAH] Uh?

487
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:27,530
Over there. Isn't that yours?

488
00:23:27,531 --> 00:23:30,449
[NOLNOA] Or rather,
what's about to happen...

489
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:32,036
I wonder.

